During the early 2000s high frequency trading was becoming more mainstream and widely spread on Wall Street

In 2009 Nav wanted so badly to beat them; so he went out to build his own software https://t.co/j0k17fSIlp

Nav traded a financial instrument called E-mini, which tracks the S&P 500 and allows traders to hedge bets and speculate on trades

He would purchase futures or options contracts and essentially bet that the market would go up or down https://t.co/gEI4AoQUBS

There has been a significant decline in the market. The market is not good for short-term bears, but is perfect for long-term bulls.
